{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876035354,"sessionID":"ses_2858a91f0ffek8sxza6i77XFZH","part":{"id":"prt_d7a75c98f001xIQNW4iVtoSzRb","messageID":"msg_d7a75b8ba001D5lMXgHBuS8Xhi","sessionID":"ses_2858a91f0ffek8sxza6i77XFZH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3fa0a17cdbe344bca27cc8df","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n2: \n3: Source root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n4: \n5: ## Architecture\n6: \n7: ### Overview\n8: \n9: The AgentCube Python SDK follows a layered architecture with clear separation between control plane and data plane operations:\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    Public API Layer                          │\n14: │  CodeInterpreterClient          AgentRuntimeClient          │\n15: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n16:                               │\n17:         ┌─────────────────────┴─────────────────────┐\n18:         │                                           │\n19:         ▼                                           ▼\n20: ┌───────────────────┐                   ┌───────────────────────┐\n21: │   Control Plane   │                   │     Data Plane        │\n22: │  ControlPlane     │                   │  CodeInterpreter      │\n23: │     Client        │                   │  DataPlaneClient      │\n24: │                   │                   │                       │\n25: │  (Session Mgmt)   │                   │  (Code/File Ops)      │\n26: └───────────────────┘                   └───────────────────────┘\n27:                                                  │\n28:                               ┌──────────────────┴──────────────┐\n29:                               │                                 │\n30:                               ▼                                 ▼\n31:                     ┌───────────────────┐           ┌───────────────────┐\n32:                     │   AgentRuntime    │           │    HTTP Client    │\n33:                     │  DataPlaneClient  │           │   Utilities       │\n34:                     │                   │           │                   │\n35:                     │  (Agent Invoke)   │           │  (Session, Auth)  │\n36:                     └───────────────────┘           └───────────────────┘\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### Component Responsibilities\n40: \n41: | Component | Responsibility |\n42: |-----------|---------------|\n43: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | High-level facade for code interpretation; orchestrates control plane session lifecycle and data plane operations |\n44: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | High-level facade for agent runtime invocations; manages session bootstrapping and payload delivery |\n45: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane HTTP client; session creation/deletion via Workload Manager |\n46: | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; code execution and file operations via Router |\n47: | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane HTTP client; agent invocation via Router |\n48: | `create_session` | HTTP session factory with connection pooling |\n49: | `read_token_from_file` | Service account token loading utility |\n50: | `get_logger` | Structured logging configuration |\n51: \n52: ### Design Patterns\n53: \n54: 1. **Facade Pattern**: `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` provide simplified interfaces to complex subsystems\n55: 2. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both high-level clients support `with` statement for automatic resource cleanup\n56: 3. **Dependency Injection**: Lower-level clients are instantiated by higher-level clients with resolved configuration\n57: 4. **Environment Configuration**: Settings resolve from constructor args → environment variables → defaults\n58: \n59: ## Data Structures\n60: \n61: ### Class Instance Attributes\n62: \n63: #### `CodeInterpreterClient`\n64: \n65: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n66: |-----------|------|-------------|\n67: | `name` | `str` | Interpreter session name (default: `\"my-interpreter\"`) |\n68: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace (default: `\"default\"`) |\n69: | `ttl` | `int` | Session time-to-live in seconds (default: `3600`) |\n70: | `verbose` | `bool` | Enable debug logging |\n71: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n72: | `cp_client` | `ControlPlaneClient` | Control plane client instance |\n73: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n74: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (provided or created) |\n75: | `dp_client` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n76: \n77: #### `AgentRuntimeClient`\n78: \n79: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n80: |-----------|------|-------------|\n81: | `agent_name` | `str` | Target agent runtime name |\n82: | `namespace` | `str` | Kubernetes namespace |\n83: | `timeout` | `int` | Default request timeout in seconds (default: `120`) |\n84: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout in seconds (default: `5.0`) |\n85: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n86: | `router_url` | `str` | Router base URL |\n87: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | Session identifier (bootstrapped or provided) |\n88: | `dp_client` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Data plane client instance |\n89: \n90: #### `ControlPlaneClient`\n91: \n92: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n93: |-----------|------|-------------|\n94: | `base_url` | `str` | Workload Manager API base URL |\n95: | `auth_token` | `str` | Bearer token for authentication |\n96: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n97: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n98: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n99: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n100: \n101: #### `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n102: \n103: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n104: |-----------|------|-------------|\n105: | `session_id` | `str` | Session identifier for header |\n106: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n107: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n108: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n109: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n110: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n111: \n112: #### `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n113: \n114: | Attribute | Type | Description |\n115: |-----------|------|-------------|\n116: | `base_url` | `str` | Computed Router invocation URL |\n117: | `timeout` | `int` | Request timeout (default: `120`) |\n118: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | Connection timeout (default: `5.0`) |\n119: | `session` | `requests.Session` | HTTP session with connection pooling |\n120: | `logger` | `logging.Logger` | Module logger instance |\n121: \n122: ### Exception Classes\n123: \n124: ```\n125: AgentCubeError (base)\n126: ├── CommandExecutionError\n127: │   ├── exit_code: int\n128: │   ├── stderr: str\n129: │   └── command: Optional[str]\n130: ├── SessionError\n131: └── DataPlaneError\n132: ```\n133: \n134: | Exception | Raised When |\n135: |-----------|-------------|\n136: | `AgentCubeError` | Base class; not raised directly |\n137: | `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command returns non-zero exit code |\n138: | `SessionError` | Reserved for session creation/management failures |\n139: | `DataPlaneError` | Reserved for data plane operation failures |\n140: \n141: ### Request/Response DTOs\n142: \n143: #### Control Plane - Create Session Request\n144: \n145: ```json\n146: {\n147:   \"name\": \"string\",\n148:   \"namespace\": \"string\",\n149:   \"ttl\": 3600,\n150:   \"metadata\": {}\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### Control Plane - Create Session Response\n155: \n156: ```json\n157: {\n158:   \"sessionId\": \"string\"\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: #### Data Plane - Execute Command Request\n163: \n164: ```json\n165: {\n166:   \"command\": [\"string\"] | \"string\",\n167:   \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n168: }\n169: ```\n170: \n171: #### Data Plane - Execute Command Response\n172: \n173: ```json\n174: {\n175:   \"stdout\": \"string\",\n176:   \"stderr\": \"string\",\n177:   \"exit_code\": 0\n178: }\n179: ```\n180: \n181: #### Data Plane - Write File Request\n182: \n183: ```json\n184: {\n185:   \"path\": \"string\",\n186:   \"content\": \"base64-encoded-string\",\n187:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n188: }\n189: ```\n190: \n191: #### Data Plane - List Files Response\n192: \n193: ```json\n194: {\n195:   \"files\": [\"string\"]\n196: }\n197: ```\n198: \n199: ## API Contracts\n200: \n201: ### Control Plane API (Workload Manager)\n202: \n203: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n204: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n205: | Create Session | POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | `CreateSessionRequest` | `sessionId: str` |\n206: | Delete Session | DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | - | `bool` |\n207: \n208: #### Create Session\n209: \n210: - **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`\n211: - **Method**: `POST`\n212: - **Headers**:\n213:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n214:   - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token present)\n215: - **Body**:\n216:   ```json\n217:   {\n218:     \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n219:     \"namespace\": \"default\",\n220:     \"ttl\": 3600,\n221:     \"metadata\": {}\n222:   }\n223:   ```\n224: - **Success Response** (200/201):\n225:   ```json\n226:   {\n227:     \"sessionId\": \"ci-abc123\"\n228:   }\n229:   ```\n230: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)` tuple\n231: \n232: #### Delete Session\n233: \n234: - **URL**: `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n235: - **Method**: `DELETE`\n236: - **Headers**: Same as Create Session\n237: - **Success Response** (200/204): `True`\n238: - **Not Found** (404): `True` (treated as idempotent success)\n239: - **Other Errors**: Log and return `False`\n240: \n241: ### Data Plane API (Code Interpreter via Router)\n242: \n243: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n244: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n245: | Execute Command | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n246: | Run Code | POST | `{base_url}api/execute` | `ExecuteCommandRequest` | `str` (stdout) |\n247: | Write File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | `WriteFileRequest` (JSON) | `None` |\n248: | Upload File | POST | `{base_url}api/files` | Multipart form | `None` |\n249: | Download File | GET | `{base_url}api/files/{path}` | - | `bytes` |\n250: | List Files | GET | `{base_url}api/files` | Query: `path` | `List[str]` |\n251: \n252: #### Execute Command\n253: \n254: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/execute`\n255: - **Method**: `POST`\n256: - **Headers**:\n257:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n258:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n259: - **Body**:\n260:   ```json\n261:   {\n262:     \"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('hello')\"],\n263:     \"timeout\": \"120s\"\n264:   }\n265:   ```\n266: - **Success Response** (200): stdout string\n267: - **Error Response**: Raises `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n268: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout_value + 2.0)` for read side\n269: \n270: #### Write File\n271: \n272: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n273: - **Method**: `POST`\n274: - **Headers**:\n275:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n276:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n277: - **Body**:\n278:   ```json\n279:   {\n280:     \"path\": \"/app/test.py\",\n281:     \"content\": \"<base64-encoded>\",\n282:     \"mode\": \"0644\"\n283:   }\n284:   ```\n285: \n286: #### Upload File (Multipart)\n287: \n288: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n289: - **Method**: `POST`\n290: - **Headers**:\n291:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n292: - **Form Data**:\n293:   - `file`: binary file content\n294:   - `path`: remote file path\n295:   - `mode`: file mode (default: `\"0644\"`)\n296: \n297: #### Download File\n298: \n299: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files/{clean_path}` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n300: - **Method**: `GET`\n301: - **Headers**:\n302:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n303: - **Query Params**: `stream=True`\n304: - **Response**: Binary file content\n305: \n306: #### List Files\n307: \n308: - **URL**: `{base_url}api/files`\n309: - **Method**: `GET`\n310: - **Headers**:\n311:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n312: - **Query Params**: `path` (default: `\".\"`)\n313: - **Response**: JSON array of file paths\n314: \n315: ### Data Plane API (Agent Runtime via Router)\n316: \n317: | Operation | HTTP Method | URL Pattern | Request Body | Response |\n318: |-----------|-------------|-------------|--------------|----------|\n319: | Bootstrap Session | GET | `{base_url}` | - | `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n320: | Invoke Agent | POST | `{base_url}` | `Dict[str, Any]` | `requests.Response` |\n321: \n322: #### Bootstrap Session ID\n323: \n324: - **URL**: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n325: - **Method**: `GET`\n326: - **Headers**: None (session default only)\n327: - **Success Response**: Header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n328: - **Error**: Raises `ValueError` if header missing\n329: \n330: #### Invoke Agent\n331: \n332: - **URL**: `{base_url}`\n333: - **Method**: `POST`\n334: - **Headers**:\n335:   - `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n336:   - `Content-Type: application/json`\n337: - **Body**: JSON payload dict\n338: - **Timeout**: `(connect_timeout, timeout)`\n339: \n340: ## Error Handling\n341: \n342: ### Exception Hierarchy\n343: \n344: ```python\n345: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n346:     \"\"\"Base exception for all AgentCube SDK errors\"\"\"\n347:     pass\n348: \n349: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n350:     \"\"\"Raised when remote command execution fails\"\"\"\n351:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: Optional[str] = None):\n352:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n353:         self.stderr = stderr\n354:         self.command = command\n355:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n356: \n357: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n358:     \"\"\"Reserved for session creation/management failures\"\"\"\n359:     pass\n360: \n361: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n362:     \"\"\"Reserved for data plane operation failures\"\"\"\n363:     pass\n364: ```\n365: \n366: ### Error Handling Strategy\n367: \n368: | Component | Error Source | Handling Strategy |\n369: |-----------|--------------|-------------------|\n370: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | `_init_data_plane()` failure | Log warning, delete session, re-raise |\n371: | `CodeInterpreterClient` | Context manager exit | Call `stop()` for cleanup regardless of exception |\n372: | `execute_command` | Non-zero exit code | Raise `CommandExecutionError` |\n373: | `ControlPlaneClient` | 404 on delete | Return `True` (idempotent) |\n374: | `ControlPlaneClient` | Other HTTP errors | Log and return `False` |\n375: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | Missing session header | Raise `ValueError` |\n376: | `AgentRuntimeClient` | Invoke without session | Raise `ValueError` |\n377: | HTTP clients | `requests.RequestException` | Propagate to caller |\n378: \n379: ### Cleanup Guarantees\n380: \n381: 1. **Context Manager Protocol**: Both `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` implement `__enter__` and `__exit__` for deterministic cleanup\n382: 2. **Stop Method**: `CodeInterpreterClient.stop()` ensures:\n383:    - Data plane session closure\n384:    - Control plane session deletion (if created internally)\n385:    - HTTP session close\n386: 3. **Close Method**: `AgentRuntimeClient.close()` ensures HTTP session closure\n387: 4. **Exception Safety**: Cleanup occurs regardless of exception type in `__exit__`\n388: \n389: ## Testing Strategy\n390: \n391: ### Test Categories\n392: \n393: | Category | Scope | Tools | Location |\n394: |----------|-------|-------|----------|\n395: | Unit Tests | Individual classes/methods | `pytest`, `unittest.mock` | `tests/unit/` |\n396: | Integration Tests | Client-server interaction | `pytest`, test fixtures | `tests/integration/` |\n397: | End-to-End Tests | Full workflow validation | `pytest`, live environment | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` |\n398: \n399: ### Unit Test Strategy\n400: \n401: #### Mocking Approach\n402: \n403: ```python\n404: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch, MagicMock\n405: import pytest\n406: \n407: # Example: Mock HTTP session\n408: @pytest.fixture\n409: def mock_session():\n410:     session = Mock(spec=requests.Session)\n411:     session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n412:     return session\n413: \n414: # Example: Patch create_session\n415: @patch('agentcube.utils.http.create_session')\n416: def test_control_plane_create_session(mock_create_session):\n417:     mock_session = Mock()\n418:     mock_session.post.return_value.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-123\"}\n419:     mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n420:     \n421:     client = ControlPlaneClient(workload_manager_url=\"http://test\")\n422:     session_id = client.create_session()\n423:     \n424:     assert session_id == \"test-123\"\n425: ```\n426: \n427: #### Test Coverage Targets\n428: \n429: | Module | Coverage Target | Key Scenarios |\n430: |--------|-----------------|---------------|\n431: | `code_interpreter.py` | 90% | Context manager, session lifecycle, delegation |\n432: | `agent_runtime.py` | 90% | Bootstrap, invoke, context manager |\n433: | `control_plane.py` | 95% | HTTP request construction, error handling |\n434: | `code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | 95% | URL construction, timeout logic, file operations |\n435: | `agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | 95% | Session bootstrap, invoke |\n436: | `utils/` | 100% | Session creation, token reading, logging |\n437: | `exceptions.py` | 100% | Exception initialization |\n438: \n439: ### Integration Test Strategy\n440: \n441: #### Test Fixtures\n442: \n443: ```python\n444: @pytest.fixture\n445: def code_interpreter_client():\n446:     client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n447:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n448:         workload_manager_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"),\n449:         namespace=\"test\"\n450:     )\n451:     yield client\n452:     client.stop()\n453: \n454: @pytest.fixture\n455: def agent_runtime_client():\n456:     client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n457:         agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n458:         router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n459:         namespace=\"test\"\n460:     )\n461:     yield client\n462:     client.close()\n463: ```\n464: \n465: #### Integration Test Scenarios\n466: \n467: | Test | Steps | Expected Outcome |\n468: |------|-------|------------------|\n469: | `test_code_execution` | Create session → Execute `print(\"hello\")` | stdout contains \"hello\" |\n470: | `test_file_operations` | Write file → List files → Download file | File exists, content matches |\n471: | `test_agent_invoke` | Bootstrap session → Invoke agent | Valid response from agent |\n472: \n473: ### End-to-End Test\n474: \n475: Located at `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py`:\n476: \n477: ```python\n478: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n479: \"\"\"End-to-end test for Code Interpreter with PicoD\"\"\"\n480: \n481: import sys\n482: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n483: \n484: def main():\n485:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n486:         router_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n487:         namespace=\"default\"\n488:     ) as client:\n489:         # Test 1: Simple command\n490:         result = client.execute_command(\"echo 'hello'\")\n491:         assert \"hello\" in result\n492:         \n493:         # Test 2: Python code\n494:         result = client.run_code(\"python\", \"print(2 + 2)\")\n495:         assert \"4\" in result\n496:         \n497:         # Test 3: File write and read\n498:         client.write_file(\"test content\", \"/app/test.txt\")\n499:         result = client.execute_command(\"cat /app/test.txt\")\n500:         assert \"test content\" in result\n501:         \n502:     print(\"All E2E tests passed!\")\n503:     return 0\n504: \n505: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n506:     sys.exit(main())\n507: ```\n508: \n509: ### Continuous Integration\n510: \n511: | Pipeline Stage | Tests | Environment |\n512: |----------------|-------|-------------|\n513: | Lint | `pytest --flake8`, `mypy` | Isolated |\n514: | Unit Test | `pytest tests/unit/` | Isolated |\n515: | Integration Test | `pytest tests/integration/` | Test cluster |\n516: | E2E Test | `scripts/e2e_picod_test.py` | Staging environment |\n517: \n518: ## Dependencies\n519: \n520: ### Runtime Dependencies\n521: \n522: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n523: |---------|---------|---------|\n524: | `requests` | `>=2.28.0` | HTTP client |\n525: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT token handling |\n526: | `cryptography` | `>=38.0.0` | Cryptographic operations |\n527: \n528: ### Build Configuration\n529: \n530: ```toml\n531: [build-system]\n532: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n533: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n534: \n535: [project]\n536: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n537: version = \"0.1.0\"\n538: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n539: dependencies = [\n540:     \"requests\",\n541:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n542:     \"cryptography\",\n543: ]\n544: \n545: [tool.setuptools.packages.find]\n546: where = [\".\"]\n547: include = [\"agentcube*\"]\n548: namespaces = false\n549: ```\n550: \n551: ### Development Dependencies\n552: \n553: | Package | Purpose |\n554: |---------|---------|\n555: | `pytest` | Test framework |\n556: | `pytest-mock` | Mocking utilities |\n557: | `pytest-cov` | Coverage reporting |\n558: | `mypy` | Static type checking |\n559: | `flake8` | Code style linting |\n560: | `black` | Code formatting |\n561: \n562: ## Logging Strategy\n563: \n564: ### Logger Configuration\n565: \n566: ```python\n567: def get_logger(name: str, level: Union[int, str] = logging.INFO) -> logging.Logger:\n568:     logger = logging.getLogger(name)\n569:     logger.setLevel(level)\n570:     \n571:     if not logger.handlers:\n572:         handler = logging.StreamHandler()\n573:         formatter = logging.Formatter(\n574:             '%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s'\n575:         )\n576:         handler.setFormatter(formatter)\n577:         logger.addHandler(handler)\n578:     \n579:     return logger\n580: ```\n581: \n582: ### Log Levels\n583: \n584: | Level | Usage |\n585: |-------|-------|\n586: | `DEBUG` | HTTP request/response details, configuration resolution |\n587: | `INFO` | Session creation/deletion, major lifecycle events |\n588: | `WARNING` | Non-critical errors (404 on delete), fallback behavior |\n589: | `ERROR` | Operation failures, exceptions |\n590: \n591: ### Example Log Output\n592: \n593: ```\n594: 2024-01-15 10:30:00 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Creating session: my-interpreter\n595: 2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.control_plane - DEBUG - POST http://wm:8080/v1/code-interpreter\n596: 2024-01-15 10:30:01 - agentcube.code_interpreter - INFO - Session created: ci-abc123\n597: 2024-01-15 10:30:02 - agentcube.data_plane - DEBUG - POST http://router:8080/.../api/execute\n598: ```\n599: \n600: ## Security Considerations\n601: \n602: ### Authentication\n603: \n604: 1. **Control Plane**: Bearer token via `Authorization` header\n605:    - Token from constructor argument `auth_token`\n606:    - Fallback to service account token file: `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n607: \n608: 2. **Data Plane**: JWT handled by Router; SDK does not set `Authorization` header\n609: \n610: ### Session ID Security\n611: \n612: - Session ID transmitted in `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n613: - Session ID should be treated as sensitive (grants access to sandbox)\n614: - Automatic session cleanup on context manager exit\n615: \n616: ### File Operations\n617: \n618: - No local file system access outside provided paths\n619: - Upload/download operations require explicit local path specification\n620: - Remote file paths validated/cleaned before use\n\n(End of file - total 620 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\nSource root: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK follows a layered architecture with clear separation between control plane and data plane operations:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Public API Layer                          │\n│  CodeInterpreterClient          AgentRuntimeClient          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n        ┌─────────────────────┴─────────────────────┐\n        │                                           │\n        ▼                                           ▼\n┌───────────────────┐                   ┌───────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/design.md","time":{"start":1775876035335,"end":1775876035351}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876035358,"sessionID":"ses_2858a91f0ffek8sxza6i77XFZH","part":{"id":"prt_d7a75ce46001hoYrG6wG1kN5XE","messageID":"msg_d7a75b8ba001D5lMXgHBuS8Xhi","sessionID":"ses_2858a91f0ffek8sxza6i77XFZH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1a12f00b86a54b83bf2191f0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Python client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\n10: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n11: \n12: #### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n13: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n14: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n15: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n16: \n17: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n18: - **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n19: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n20: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Router URL required\n23: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n24: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n25: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n26: \n27: ### Requirement: Code Interpreter — execute, files, stop\n28: The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Command non-zero exit\n31: - **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n32: - **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n33: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Python code execution path\n36: - **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n37: - **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n38: - **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: `AgentRuntimeClient` lifecycle\n41: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL, then `POST` JSON payloads with session header.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Context manager\n44: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n45: - **WHEN** the block exits\n46: - **THEN** `close()` SHALL close the underlying `requests.Session`\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Bootstrap session id\n49: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n50: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n51: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET` `{router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`; if missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Invoke without session\n54: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy\n55: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n56: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n57: \n58: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — control plane\n59: The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: Create session\n62: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n63: - **WHEN** the request succeeds\n64: - **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Delete session\n67: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n68: - **WHEN** the server returns 404\n69: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Workload Manager URL and auth\n72: - **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n73: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n74: - **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n75: \n76: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Code Interpreter)\n77: The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: Execute command\n80: - **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n81: - **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Files API\n84: - **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n86: - **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n87: - **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n88: \n89: ### Requirement: HTTP client contracts — data plane (Agent Runtime)\n90: The system SHALL `POST` JSON to the invocation base URL with headers `x-agentcube-session-id` and `Content-Type: application/json`.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple\n93: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)`\n94: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n95: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: Session header management\n98: The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests (`CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` default session header; `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` uses class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`).\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Code Interpreter session header\n101: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n102: - **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n103: - **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Exception hierarchy\n106: The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Command failure\n109: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n110: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n111: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: SessionError / DataPlaneError usage\n114: - **GIVEN** the current package sources under `agentcube/`\n115: - **WHEN** searching for `raise SessionError` / `raise DataPlaneError`\n116: - **THEN** these classes are defined for extension but not raised by the core client modules in the extracted tree (callers MAY rely on `ValueError`, `requests` exceptions, or `CommandExecutionError`)\n117: \n118: ### Requirement: Timeout behavior\n119: The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Per-call override for code execution\n122: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n123: - **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n124: - **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeClient constructor timeouts\n127: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient(..., timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`\n128: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called without `timeout`\n129: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `120` (instance default)\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: **Public package surface:** `agentcube/__init__.py` exports only `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`.\n\n(End of file - total 133 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nPython client library (`agentcube-sdk`) for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads through the Router.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: `CodeInterpreterClient` lifecycle\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/python-sdk/spec.md","time":{"start":1775876035340,"end":1775876035355}}}}
