{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876155168,"sessionID":"ses_2858a91f0ffek8sxza6i77XFZH","part":{"id":"prt_d7a760a0c0011Z7HkKHZWtkBwb","messageID":"msg_d7a75e6f60015Xec6zzO7e3hS3","sessionID":"ses_2858a91f0ffek8sxza6i77XFZH","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_17f3c749211e46deb9e858c1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_028.md","content":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal implements the `AgentRuntimeClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK (`sdk-python`). The goal is to:\n\n1. **Provide high-level agent invocation** - Abstract session bootstrapping and payload delivery to Agent Runtime workloads\n2. **Enable agent communication** - Invoke agent runtimes with arbitrary JSON payloads through the Router\n3. **Support context management** - Context manager protocol for automatic session cleanup and resource deallocation\n4. **Ensure session lifecycle** - Bootstrap or reuse session ID from Agent Runtime invocation endpoint\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - `AgentRuntimeClient` class with context manager support\n  - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for data plane HTTP operations via Router\n  - Session bootstrapping via GET on invocation endpoint\n  - Payload invocation via POST with session header\n  - HTTP session management with connection pooling\n  - Timeout configuration and per-call overrides\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - Direct user-facing CLI commands (separate AR)\n  - Kubernetes CRD management (handled by CLI toolkit)\n  - Code Interpreter functionality (covered by AR-027)\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Implementation\n\nPer the design specification (`python-sdk/design.md`), the following components are defined:\n\n1. **Package Layout:**\n   - `agentcube/__init__.py` - Public exports (`CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`)\n   - `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` - `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation\n   - `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` - `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation\n   - `agentcube/utils/http.py` - `create_session` for HTTP session management\n   - `agentcube/utils/log.py` - `get_logger` for logging configuration\n\n2. **Configuration Pattern:**\n   - No single `Configuration` class\n   - Distributed configuration: `AgentRuntimeClient` resolves `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` environment variable\n   - Timeout defaults: `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n\n3. **HTTP Contracts:**\n   - Bootstrap: `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n   - Invoke: `POST {base_url}` with JSON payload and `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n\n### Issues Identified\n\n1. **Session header naming** - Must use lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for consistency with Code Interpreter\n2. **Bootstrap validation** - Must raise `ValueError` if `x-agentcube-session-id` header is missing from bootstrap response\n3. **Invoke precondition** - Must raise `ValueError` if `invoke()` is called without initialized `session_id`\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. AgentRuntimeClient Implementation\n\nImplement in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom .clients.agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\nfrom .utils.log import get_logger\n\n\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    \"\"\"High-level client for invoking Agent Runtime workloads.\n    \n    This client manages the session lifecycle for Agent Runtime invocations,\n    supporting both explicit session ID provision and automatic bootstrapping\n    from the Router invocation endpoint.\n    \n    Example usage:\n        # Context manager pattern (recommended)\n        with AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        ) as client:\n            response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n            print(response.json())\n        \n        # Explicit session ID\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n            session_id=\"pre-existing-session\"\n        )\n        try:\n            response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n        finally:\n            client.close()\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize AgentRuntimeClient.\n        \n        Args:\n            agent_name: Name of the target agent runtime\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace (default: \"default\")\n            router_url: Router base URL. Resolves from arg or ROUTER_URL env var\n            verbose: Enable debug logging\n            session_id: Existing session ID. If None, bootstraps new session\n            timeout: Default request timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n            connect_timeout: Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n        \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If router_url not provided and ROUTER_URL env var not set\n        \"\"\"\n        self.agent_name = agent_name\n        self.namespace = namespace\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__, level=\"DEBUG\" if verbose else \"INFO\")\n        \n        # Resolve router_url from argument or environment\n        self.router_url = router_url or os.getenv(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n        if not self.router_url:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL environment variable must be set\"\n            )\n        \n        self.session_id = session_id\n        \n        # Initialize data plane client\n        self.dp_client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=self.router_url,\n            namespace=self.namespace,\n            agent_name=self.agent_name,\n            timeout=self.timeout,\n            connect_timeout=self.connect_timeout,\n        )\n        \n        # Bootstrap session if not provided\n        if not self.session_id:\n            self.session_id = self.dp_client.bootstrap_session_id()\n            self.logger.debug(f\"Bootstrapped session_id: {self.session_id}\")\n    \n    def __enter__(self) -> \"AgentRuntimeClient\":\n        \"\"\"Context manager entry.\"\"\"\n        return self\n    \n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Context manager exit - ensures cleanup.\"\"\"\n        self.close()\n    \n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Invoke the agent runtime with a JSON payload.\n        \n        Args:\n            payload: JSON-serializable dict to send to the agent\n            timeout: Optional per-call timeout override. If None, uses instance default\n        \n        Returns:\n            Agent response (typically parsed JSON or response object)\n        \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If session_id is not initialized\n        \n        Example:\n            response = client.invoke({\n                \"action\": \"query\",\n                \"parameters\": {\"key\": \"value\"}\n            })\n        \"\"\"\n        if not self.session_id:\n            raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")\n        \n        self.logger.debug(f\"Invoking agent {self.agent_name} with payload: {payload}\")\n        \n        response = self.dp_client.invoke(\n            session_id=self.session_id,\n            payload=payload,\n            timeout=timeout,\n        )\n        \n        # Return parsed JSON response\n        return response.json()\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the underlying HTTP session.\n        \n        This method should be called when the client is no longer needed,\n        or use the context manager protocol for automatic cleanup.\n        \"\"\"\n        self.dp_client.close()\n        self.logger.debug(\"AgentRuntimeClient closed\")\n```\n\n### 2. AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Implementation\n\nImplement in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\nfrom urllib.parse import urljoin\n\nimport requests\n\nfrom ..utils.http import create_session\nfrom ..utils.log import get_logger\n\n\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    \"\"\"Low-level HTTP client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n    \n    This client handles direct HTTP communication with the Router's\n    Agent Runtime invocation endpoint.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n    \n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Initialize AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.\n        \n        Args:\n            router_url: Router base URL\n            namespace: Kubernetes namespace\n            agent_name: Target agent runtime name\n            timeout: Request timeout in seconds (default: 120)\n            connect_timeout: Connection timeout in seconds (default: 5.0)\n            pool_connections: Number of connection pool slots\n            pool_maxsize: Maximum connections per host\n        \"\"\"\n        self.timeout = timeout\n        self.connect_timeout = connect_timeout\n        self.logger = get_logger(__name__)\n        \n        # Compute base URL: {router}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{agent}/invocations/\n        base_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n        self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n        \n        # Create HTTP session with connection pooling\n        self.session = create_session(\n            pool_connections=pool_connections,\n            pool_maxsize=pool_maxsize,\n        )\n        \n        # Set default session header\n        self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] = \"\"  # Set per-request\n    \n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Bootstrap a new session ID from the invocation endpoint.\n        \n        Makes a GET request to the base invocation URL to obtain\n        a session ID from the response header.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Session ID from x-agentcube-session-id header\n        \n        Raises:\n            ValueError: If x-agentcube-session-id header is missing\n        \"\"\"\n        self.logger.debug(f\"Bootstrapping session from {self.base_url}\")\n        \n        response = self.session.get(\n            self.base_url,\n            timeout=(self.connect_timeout, self.timeout),\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        \n        session_id = response.headers.get(\"x-agentcube-session-id\")\n        if not session_id:\n            raise ValueError(\n                \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"\n            )\n        \n        # Set session header for subsequent requests\n        self.session.headers[\"x-agentcube-session-id\"] = session_id\n        \n        return session_id\n    \n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response:\n        \"\"\"Invoke the agent runtime with a JSON payload.\n        \n        Args:\n            session_id: Session identifier for request header\n            payload: JSON-serializable dict to send\n            timeout: Optional timeout override. If tuple, uses (connect, read)\n        \n        Returns:\n            requests.Response object from the POST request\n        \n        Raises:\n            requests.RequestException: On HTTP errors\n        \"\"\"\n        # Set session header for this request\n        headers = {self.SESSION_HEADER: session_id, \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}\n        \n        # Compute effective timeout\n        if timeout is None:\n            effective_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, self.timeout)\n        elif isinstance(timeout, tuple):\n            effective_timeout = timeout\n        else:\n            effective_timeout = (self.connect_timeout, timeout)\n        \n        self.logger.debug(f\"POST {self.base_url} with payload: {payload}\")\n        \n        response = self.session.post(\n            self.base_url,\n            json=payload,\n            headers=headers,\n            timeout=effective_timeout,\n        )\n        \n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response\n    \n    def close(self) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Close the underlying HTTP session.\"\"\"\n        self.session.close()\n        self.logger.debug(\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient closed\")\n```\n\n### 3. Module Exports\n\nUpdate `agentcube/__init__.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\nfrom .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n__all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n```\n\nUpdate `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`:\n\n```python\nfrom .control_plane import ControlPlaneClient\nfrom .code_interpreter_data_plane import CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\nfrom .agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n__all__ = [\n    \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n    \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n    \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n]\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` implementation |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` implementation |\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n| File | Changes | Impact |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Export `AgentRuntimeClient` | Low - additive |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Re-export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Low - convenience |\n\n### Dependencies\n\nFrom `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"requests\",              # HTTP client\n    \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",         # JWT token handling (if needed)\n    \"cryptography\",          # Cryptographic operations (if needed)\n]\n\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n```\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- **No breaking changes** - This is a new feature addition\n- **Session header consistency** - Uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` matching Code Interpreter\n- **Timeout defaults** - Consistent 120s read / 5.0s connect defaults across all clients\n\n### Testing Impact\n\nUnit tests required for:\n\n- `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__()` with/without session_id\n- `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` payload delivery\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` context manager cleanup\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.bootstrap_session_id()` header extraction\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke()` timeout handling\n- Error cases: missing router_url, missing session header, invoke without session\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Reuse CodeInterpreterClient Pattern\n\nExtend `CodeInterpreterClient` to support agent invocation.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Single client class for both use cases\n- Shared session management logic\n\n**Cons:**\n- Violates single responsibility principle\n- Confuses distinct use cases (code execution vs agent invocation)\n- Different HTTP contracts (Code Interpreter has files API, Agent Runtime does not)\n\n**Decision:** Separate client classes maintain clear separation of concerns.\n\n### Alternative 2: Async/Await HTTP Client\n\nUse `aiohttp` instead of `requests` for async operations.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Better performance for concurrent invocations\n- Modern async pattern\n\n**Cons:**\n- Breaking change from synchronous Code Interpreter pattern\n- Requires async context manager support throughout\n- Increased complexity for users unfamiliar with async\n\n**Decision:** Synchronous `requests` maintains consistency with existing SDK.\n\n### Alternative 3: Session ID from Control Plane\n\nBootstrap session ID via control plane instead of data plane GET.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Centralized session management\n- Consistent with Code Interpreter session creation\n\n**Cons:**\n- Requires control plane API changes\n- Agent Runtime sessions are Router-scoped, not Workload Manager-scoped\n- Adds unnecessary round-trip\n\n**Decision:** Bootstrap via data plane GET is more direct and aligns with Router architecture.\n\n### Alternative 4: Explicit Session Management\n\nRequire users to always provide session_id explicitly.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Simpler implementation (no bootstrap logic)\n- Users have full control over session lifecycle\n\n**Cons:**\n- Poor user experience (must manage sessions externally)\n- Loses convenience of context manager pattern\n- Inconsistent with CodeInterpreterClient pattern\n\n**Decision:** Automatic bootstrapping provides better developer experience.\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` in `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n- [ ] Export `AgentRuntimeClient` in `agentcube/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Export `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` in `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write unit tests for session bootstrapping\n- [ ] Write unit tests for invoke with/without timeout\n- [ ] Write unit tests for context manager cleanup\n- [ ] Write integration tests with live Router endpoint\n- [ ] Add usage examples to `examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`\n- [ ] Update README with AgentRuntimeClient documentation\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/unit/test_agent_runtime.py\n\nimport pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import Mock, patch\nfrom agentcube.agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\nfrom agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeClient:\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n    def test_init_with_session_id(self, mock_dp_client):\n        \"\"\"Test initialization with explicit session_id.\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=\"pre-existing-session\"\n        )\n        \n        assert client.session_id == \"pre-existing-session\"\n        mock_dp_client.assert_called_once()\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n    def test_init_without_session_id_bootstrap(self, mock_dp_client):\n        \"\"\"Test initialization triggers bootstrap.\"\"\"\n        mock_dp_client.return_value.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = \"bootstrapped-123\"\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        \n        assert client.session_id == \"bootstrapped-123\"\n        mock_dp_client.return_value.bootstrap_session_id.assert_called_once()\n    \n    @patch.dict('os.environ', {}, clear=True)\n    def test_init_missing_router_url_raises(self):\n        \"\"\"Test missing router_url raises ValueError.\"\"\"\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"router_url must be provided\"):\n            AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\")\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n    def test_invoke_success(self, mock_dp_client):\n        \"\"\"Test successful invoke.\"\"\"\n        mock_response = Mock()\n        mock_response.json.return_value = {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_dp_client.return_value.invoke.return_value = mock_response\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            session_id=\"test-session\"\n        )\n        \n        result = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n        \n        assert result == {\"result\": \"success\"}\n        mock_dp_client.return_value.invoke.assert_called_once()\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n    def test_invoke_without_session_raises(self, mock_dp_client):\n        \"\"\"Test invoke without session_id raises ValueError.\"\"\"\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        )\n        client.session_id = None  # Simulate uninitialized state\n        \n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"session_id is not initialized\"):\n            client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient')\n    def test_context_manager(self, mock_dp_client):\n        \"\"\"Test context manager cleanup.\"\"\"\n        with AgentRuntimeClient(\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\"\n        ) as client:\n            assert client is not None\n        \n        mock_dp_client.return_value.close.assert_called_once()\n\n\nclass TestAgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session')\n    def test_bootstrap_session_id_success(self, mock_create_session):\n        \"\"\"Test successful session bootstrap.\"\"\"\n        mock_session = Mock()\n        mock_session.get.return_value.headers = {\n            \"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"bootstrapped-456\"\n        }\n        mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        \n        session_id = client.bootstrap_session_id()\n        \n        assert session_id == \"bootstrapped-456\"\n        mock_session.get.assert_called_once()\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session')\n    def test_bootstrap_session_id_missing_header_raises(self, mock_create_session):\n        \"\"\"Test missing session header raises ValueError.\"\"\"\n        mock_session = Mock()\n        mock_session.get.return_value.headers = {}\n        mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        \n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"Missing required response header\"):\n            client.bootstrap_session_id()\n    \n    @patch('agentcube.clients.agent_runtime_data_plane.create_session')\n    def test_invoke_with_timeout_override(self, mock_create_session):\n        \"\"\"Test invoke with per-call timeout override.\"\"\"\n        mock_session = Mock()\n        mock_create_session.return_value = mock_session\n        \n        client = AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient(\n            router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n            namespace=\"default\",\n            agent_name=\"test-agent\"\n        )\n        \n        client.invoke(session_id=\"test-123\", payload={\"msg\": \"hi\"}, timeout=60)\n        \n        # Verify timeout was overridden\n        call_args = mock_session.post.call_args\n        assert call_args[1][\"timeout\"] == (5.0, 60)  # (connect, read)\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```python\n# tests/integration/test_agent_runtime_integration.py\n\nimport os\nimport pytest\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef agent_runtime_client():\n    \"\"\"Integration test fixture.\"\"\"\n    client = AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=os.getenv(\"TEST_AGENT_NAME\", \"test-agent\"),\n        router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n        namespace=\"test\"\n    )\n    yield client\n    client.close()\n\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_agent_invoke_full_flow(agent_runtime_client):\n    \"\"\"Test full agent invocation flow.\"\"\"\n    response = agent_runtime_client.invoke({\n        \"action\": \"echo\",\n        \"message\": \"integration test\"\n    })\n    \n    assert response is not None\n    assert \"message\" in response or \"result\" in response\n\n\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_context_manager_cleanup():\n    \"\"\"Test context manager ensures cleanup.\"\"\"\n    with AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=os.getenv(\"TEST_AGENT_NAME\", \"test-agent\"),\n        router_url=os.getenv(\"TEST_ROUTER_URL\"),\n        namespace=\"test\"\n    ) as client:\n        response = client.invoke({\"action\": \"test\"})\n        assert response is not None\n    \n    # Client closed automatically\n```\n\n### End-to-End Test\n\n```python\n# scripts/e2e_agent_runtime_test.py\n\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"End-to-end test for Agent Runtime Client\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nfrom agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient\n\n\ndef main():\n    with AgentRuntimeClient(\n        agent_name=\"echo-agent\",\n        router_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n        namespace=\"default\"\n    ) as client:\n        # Test 1: Simple invoke\n        response = client.invoke({\"message\": \"hello\"})\n        assert \"message\" in response or \"result\" in response\n        \n        # Test 2: Complex payload\n        response = client.invoke({\n            \"action\": \"compute\",\n            \"data\": {\"a\": 1, \"b\": 2}\n        })\n        assert response is not None\n        \n    print(\"All Agent Runtime E2E tests passed!\")\n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    sys.exit(main())\n```\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Streaming responses** - Support for streaming agent responses via SSE or chunked transfer\n2. **Retry logic** - Automatic retry with exponential backoff for transient failures\n3. **Async support** - Async/await variant for concurrent agent invocations\n4. **Agent discovery** - List available agent runtimes in namespace\n5. **Session metadata** - Expose session metadata (creation time, TTL) from bootstrap response\n6. **Batch invocations** - Support for batch processing multiple payloads\n\n## References\n\n- SDK Design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- SDK Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Code Interpreter Client: AR-027\n- Router API: `session-router/design.md`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| Criterion | Verification |\n|-----------|--------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` bootstraps session | GET invocation URL returns `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` reuses session_id | Explicit session_id skips bootstrap |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke()` sends payload | POST with JSON body and session header |\n| Context manager cleanup | `close()` called on exit |\n| Missing router_url raises | `ValueError` when neither arg nor env var set |\n| Missing session header raises | `ValueError` if bootstrap response lacks header |\n| Invoke without session raises | `ValueError` if `invoke()` called without session_id |\n| Timeout override works | Per-call `timeout` parameter honored |\n| Exports in `__all__` | `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient` works |\n\n---\n\n**Document Version:** 1.0  \n**Last Updated:** 2026-04-11  \n**Author:** AgentCube Team  \n**Contact:** agentcube@volcano.sh  \n**AR:** AR-028  \n**Module:** `sdk-python`\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_028.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/proposal_ar_028.md","time":{"start":177587615515